        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 12:55PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1253 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Pine Springs. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Culberson County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
